reviewText: Great Concert, but video quality very grainy. With better picture quality this is a 5 star concert!
I guess I didn't how old THIS CD wavso old! It's ok anyways..

Watch it last Friday. Couldn't believe how Raspy the lead singers voice was. A great look back as I started listening to Nazareth back in the late 70's. "Hair of the Dog" was the record that got me to listen to them. Thanks

Nazareth must have been novices to Live performances.  I was not impressed by any thing on this DVD.  I brought it
for "Love Hurts" The DVD version doesn't sound anything like the version heard on radio 80's Rock.
I love Nazareth, but very disappointed with this concert. I was hoping for a bit more "rock", but they looked really out of it!

There are a couple of offical dvd's showing the recent version of Nazareth out there.  They are very very good.  They were awesome to watch until I got this.  This is Classic line up Naz, circa 1985 and the band kicks major a**.  Even though the show is about an hr long, the band tear through 12 or so songs like they just released the songs on record. Great video, great sound, great concert.  Now bring on some 70's era live band stuff.
